{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Meet Tony. He's my student."},{"time":2000,"text":"He's about my age,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and he's in San Quentin State Prison."},{"time":7000,"text":"When Tony was 16 years old,"},{"time":10000,"text":"one day, one moment,"},{"time":13000,"text":"\"It was mom's gun."},{"time":15000,"text":"Just flash it, scare the guy. He's a punk."},{"time":17000,"text":"He took some money; we'll take his money. That'll teach him."},{"time":19000,"text":"Then last minute, I'm thinking, 'Can't do this. This is wrong.'"},{"time":22000,"text":"My buddy says, 'C'mon, let's do this.'"},{"time":24000,"text":"I say, 'Let's do this.'\""},{"time":29000,"text":"And those three words, Tony's going to remember,"},{"time":31000,"text":"because the next thing he knows, he hears the pop."},{"time":33000,"text":"There's the punk on the ground, puddle of blood."},{"time":35000,"text":"And that's felony murder --"},{"time":37000,"text":"25 to life, parole at 50 if you're lucky,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and Tony's not feeling very lucky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"So when we meet in my philosophy class in his prison"},{"time":45000,"text":"and I say, \"In this class, we will discuss the foundations of ethics,\""},{"time":49000,"text":"Tony interrupts me."},{"time":51000,"text":"\"What are you going to teach me about right and wrong?"},{"time":53000,"text":"I know what is wrong. I have done wrong."},{"time":56000,"text":"I am told every day,"},{"time":58000,"text":"by every face I see, every wall I face, that I am wrong."},{"time":61000,"text":"If I ever get out of here, there will always be a mark by my name."},{"time":64000,"text":"I'm a convict; I am branded 'wrong.'"},{"time":66000,"text":"What are you going to tell me about right and wrong?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"So I say to Tony,"},{"time":72000,"text":"\"Sorry, but it's worse than you think."},{"time":75000,"text":"You think you know right and wrong?"},{"time":77000,"text":"Then can you tell me what wrong is?"},{"time":79000,"text":"No, don't just give me an example."},{"time":81000,"text":"I want to know about wrongness itself, the idea of wrong."},{"time":84000,"text":"What is that idea?"},{"time":86000,"text":"What makes something wrong?"},{"time":88000,"text":"How do we know that it's wrong? Maybe you and I disagree."},{"time":91000,"text":"Maybe one of us is wrong about the wrong."},{"time":93000,"text":"Maybe it's you, maybe it's me -- but we're not here to trade opinions;"},{"time":95000,"text":"everyone's got an opinion."},{"time":97000,"text":"We are here for knowledge."},{"time":99000,"text":"Our enemy is thoughtlessness. This is philosophy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"And something changes for Tony."},{"time":108000,"text":"\"Could be I'm wrong. I'm tired of being wrong."},{"time":111000,"text":"I want to know what is wrong."},{"time":113000,"text":"I want to know what I know.\""},{"time":115000,"text":"What Tony sees in that moment is the project of philosophy,"},{"time":118000,"text":"the project that begins in wonder --"},{"time":120000,"text":"what Kant called \"admiration and awe"},{"time":122000,"text":"at the starry sky above and the moral law within.\""},{"time":125000,"text":"What can creatures like us know of such things?"},{"time":127000,"text":"It is the project that always takes us back to the condition of existence --"},{"time":130000,"text":"what Heidegger called \"the always already there.\""},{"time":133000,"text":"It is the project of questioning what we believe and why we believe it --"},{"time":136000,"text":"what Socrates called \"the examined life.\""},{"time":138000,"text":"Socrates, a man wise enough to know that he knows nothing."},{"time":141000,"text":"Socrates died in prison,"},{"time":144000,"text":"his philosophy intact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"So Tony starts doing his homework."},{"time":149000,"text":"He learns his whys and wherefores, his causes and correlations,"},{"time":151000,"text":"his logic, his fallacies."},{"time":153000,"text":"Turns out, Tony's got the philosophy muscle."},{"time":155000,"text":"His body is in prison, but his mind is free."},{"time":157000,"text":"Tony learns about the ontologically promiscuous,"},{"time":159000,"text":"the epistemologically anxious,"},{"time":161000,"text":"the ethically dubious, the metaphysically ridiculous."},{"time":164000,"text":"That's Plato, Descartes, Nietzsche"},{"time":166000,"text":"and Bill Clinton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"So when he gives me his final paper,"},{"time":171000,"text":"in which he argues that the categorical imperative"},{"time":173000,"text":"is perhaps too uncompromising"},{"time":175000,"text":"to deal with the conflict that affects our everyday"},{"time":177000,"text":"and challenges me to tell him"},{"time":179000,"text":"whether therefore we are condemned to moral failure,"},{"time":181000,"text":"I say, \"I don't know."},{"time":183000,"text":"Let us think about that.\""},{"time":185000,"text":"Because in that moment, there's no mark by Tony's name;"},{"time":187000,"text":"it's just the two of us standing there."},{"time":189000,"text":"It is not professor and convict,"},{"time":191000,"text":"it is just two minds ready to do philosophy."},{"time":193000,"text":"And I say to Tony,"},{"time":195000,"text":"\"Let's do this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}